🧩 Features
1. Grid-Based Maze (10×10)
Fixed grid size: 10 × 10
Each cell represents:
⬜ Empty cell
🧱 Wall
🟢 Start node (fixed position)
🔴 End node (fixed position)

2. User Interaction
Click → Toggle walls
Click + Drag → Draw continuous walls
Controls:
Set Start (optional override if allowed)
Set End (optional override if allowed)
Clear Grid
Generate Random Maze

3. Maze Generation (Important Constraint)
Random maze generation always guarantees a valid solution path
Start and End nodes are predefined and fixed
Maze is generated in a way that ensures:
Connectivity between Start and End
No unsolvable configurations

4. Movement Constraints
Movement is restricted to:
Up ⬆️
Down ⬇️
Left ⬅️
Right ➡️
❌ No diagonal movement
❌ Cannot pass through walls
❌ Cannot move outside grid bounds

5. Algorithms Implemented
Breadth-First Search (BFS)
Guarantees shortest path
Explores level-by-level
Depth-First Search (DFS)
Explores deeply before backtracking
Useful for comparison
(Optional Enhancement)
A* (Heuristic-based optimal pathfinding)

6. Visualization
The application provides smooth, step-by-step animations:
🔵 Explored nodes
🟡 Final shortest path
⏱ Animated execution (~50ms delay per step)

7. Output Metrics
After execution, the app displays:
✅ Shortest path length
🔍 Number of nodes explored
⏱ Time taken (optional)
